<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3802.4.3>
    bibo:endPage "468" ;
    bibo:issue "4" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:startPage "459" ;
    bibo:volume "3802" ;
    dc:creator "Lisi, Oscar; Sabella, Giorgio; Pilato, Giovanni" ;
    dc:date "2014" ;
    dc:title "Mixibius parvus sp. nov. and Diphascon (Diphascon) ziliense sp. nov., two new species of Eutardigrada from Sicily" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.226827>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.226828> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.226827>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1 A – D, Mixibius parvus sp. nov. (Holotype). A, Detail of the cuticular ornamentation. B, Bucco-pharyngeal apparatus. Pharyngeal apophyses (arrow) and placoids are in focus. C, The hook-shaped dorsal apophysis for the insertion of the stylet muscles is clearly visible. Arrows indicate the cuticular thickenings of the buccal tube wall following the hookshaped apophyses for the insertion of the stylet muscles. D, The hook-shaped ventral apophysis for the insertion of the stylet muscles is clearly visible. Arrows indicate the cuticular thickenings of the buccal tube wall following the hook-shaped apophyses for the insertion of the stylet muscles. (The photos B, C and D are of the same specimen in different orientations as this newly mounted animal was moved to provide the appropriate images.) (Scale bar = 10 µm)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/226827/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.226828>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2 A – D, Mixibius parvus sp. nov. (holotype). A, B, claws of the third pair of legs. It is evident that the external claws are of the Isohypsibius type and the internal claws of the modified Isohypsibius type. C, Claws of the hind pair of legs. Arrow indicates the accessory points. D, Claws of the hind pair of legs. Arrow indicates a visible lunule. (Scale bar = 10 µm)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/226828/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

